data.description:
You couldn't ask for a better location, smack dab in the heart of the North Central Corridor. This beautiful condo offers privacy, convenience, and a touch of charm. The unit has an oversized front patio, big enough for a sitting area, as well as a lockable storage unit that includes a brand new water heater. The inside of the unit it beautiful, clean, and updated. The space is complete with a wood burning fire plane and custom handmade mantle, in unit W&D that are both brand new. Laundry closet also has handmade, hardwood shelving. Unit has new Hunter ceiling fans, brand new stove, fridge and dishwasher were both replaced in 2019, AC unit was replaced in 2015. Kitchen has breakfast bar, under cabinet lighting and brand new granite countertops. All new lighting fixtures throughout. Brand new paint floor to ceiling, and brand new carpet was just installed.

One of the best locations in Phoenix, close to everything, all the best restaurants, downtown, and the 51 freeway. And for anyone that enjoys a morning walk/run, the private complex backs right up to the canal. You can walk out your front door and be through the private gate and on the jogging path in 60 seconds. It’s very peaceful beneath the 100 year old giant eucalyptus trees, I used it all the time.

This isn’t the cheapest unit in town, but it’s priced fairly. It needs an owner that is looking for a reliable, private home, in a great location.

Schedule a showing today! :)



Owner pays HOA.
